first_reading.text:
[[Pr 8,22]]"The LORD begot me, the first-born of his ways, the forerunner of his prodigies of long ago;
[[Pr 8,23]]From of old I was poured forth, at the first, before the earth.
[[Pr 8,24]]When there were no depths I was brought forth, when there were no fountains or springs of water;
[[Pr 8,25]]Before the mountains were settled into place, before the hills, I was brought forth;
[[Pr 8,26]]While as yet the earth and the fields were not made, nor the first clods of the world.
[[Pr 8,27]]"When he established the heavens I was there, when he marked out the vault over the face of the deep;
[[Pr 8,28]]When he made firm the skies above, when he fixed fast the foundations of the earth;
[[Pr 8,29]]When he set for the sea its limit, so that the waters should not transgress his command;
[[Pr 8,30]]Then was I beside him as his craftsman, and I was his delight day by day, Playing before him all the while,
[[Pr 8,31]]playing on the surface of his earth; and I found delight in the sons of men.
